	<tr>
		<td colspan="2"><hr class="sep" /><a href="http://nesdev.com/NES_ADAPTER.txt" class="postlink">http://nesdev.com/NES_ADAPTER.txt</a>
<br />
<br />Keep in mind though that the CHR /A13 and A13 are mislabeled.  But if you blindly follow the pin numberings you'll be fine.  I think the error stems back to the old error kevtris made in the NES cart types doc I pointed out awhile back. (BTW if anyone plans to fix it I noticed the same issue in the rom pinouts doc as well)
<br />
<br />I made this using that schematic, a cheapo SMB glob top cart, and the mobo side of a bum 72 pin connector.  If you do it right you can keep the CIC off the original cart.
<br />
<br /><a href="http://nesdev.com/bbs/viewtopic.php?t=7263&amp;highlight=" class="postlink">http://nesdev.com/bbs/viewtopic.php?t=7263&amp;highlight=</a>
<br />Sorry my images are HUGE one of my first posts... <img src="./images/smilies/icon_wink.gif" alt=";)" title="Wink" />

		

